    "notes": "Proves the size trigger (call 1 fires at the 3rd enqueue and carries exactly 3 events, not 4) and that a single batch MAY mix streamId (s1/s2) and eventName. Each event is self-contained. The trailing flush() drains the 4th event and awaits all in-flight sends so the captured set is deterministic (SPEC.md §12.3, §12.4)."
